VITE_SITE_NAME=Northstar Market Intelligence
VITE_HERO_TITLE=Pressure-test your next product idea with qualified operator feedback
VITE_HERO_SUBTITLE=Launch a focused research landing page, capture high-intent interest, and learn which positioning gets busy decision-makers to respond.
VITE_CTA_TEXT=Join the pilot list
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3001
VITE_ENV_NAME=northstar-dev
VITE_HERO_IMAGE_URL=https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1552664730-d307ca884978?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1200&q=80
VITE_SECTION_IMAGE_URL=https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1522202176988-66273c2fd55f?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1200&q=80
VITE_BRAND_COLOR=#0f766e
VITE_FEATURE_1_TITLE=Audience signal capture
VITE_FEATURE_1_DESCRIPTION=Identify whether founders, operators, and analysts actually engage with your core market narrative.
VITE_FEATURE_2_TITLE=Dedicated lead pipeline
VITE_FEATURE_2_DESCRIPTION=Route every submission through a backend API that tags leads with the environment and business identity.
VITE_FEATURE_3_TITLE=Reusable campaign system
VITE_FEATURE_3_DESCRIPTION=Duplicate the launch pattern for the next business by changing configuration instead of rewriting application code.

# FAQ content used by the accordion section
VITE_FAQ_1_QUESTION=How is this landing page reused for another business?
VITE_FAQ_1_ANSWER=Update the Vite environment variables for the site name, copy, images, brand color, API base URL, and FAQ content. The same frontend code renders the new campaign.
VITE_FAQ_2_QUESTION=Where do submitted leads go?
VITE_FAQ_2_ANSWER=The frontend posts to the campaign API endpoint, which invokes Lambda. Lambda validates the payload, tags the lead with env and business context, and writes it to DynamoDB.
VITE_FAQ_3_QUESTION=Can I change the FAQ questions per deployment?
VITE_FAQ_3_ANSWER=Yes. Each question and answer is driven by its own env variable so Business A, Business B, and Business C can all use the same code with different copy.
